cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper discusses the Hirsch index and its variants for an exploratory factor analysis, which is a topic related to bibliometrics and scientometrics. This makes cs.DL (Digital Libraries) the most likely sub-category. The paper also analyzes citation records, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). The use of logarithmic and square-root transformation of data suggests a focus on mathematical and statistical methods, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
